                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Hobbyists and Geeks Make the Internet Strong]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ways-hobbyists-accidentally-future-proofed-the-internet/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/teletype-with-video-terminal.jpg" length="1491" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[History]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cloud & Internet]]></category><category><![CDATA[Open Source]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Glory to the tinkerers.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The internet is almost certainly the most complex machine humanity has ever created. You might not notice it simply because, most of the time, the internet and services like the Web work without a hitch, but under the hood there's an enormous number of things that have to all work together seamlessly.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 20:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/ways-hobbyists-accidentally-future-proofed-the-internet/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[AirPods Pro 3 vs. AirPods Pro 2: Is It Time for an Upgrade?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/airpods-pro-3-vs-airpods-pro-2/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/airpods-pro-4-new-design-and-tips.jpg" length="186" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple AirPods Pro 3]]></category><category><![CDATA[AirPods Pro]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[headphones]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Battle of the best buds.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>September 2025 saw some big announcements from Apple, including a brand new iPhone, three Apple Watch refreshes, and the arrival of the long-awaited AirPods Pro 3.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 20:01:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/airpods-pro-3-vs-airpods-pro-2/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Google Explains How It Pulled Off Meet's Live Translation]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/google-explains-how-it-pulled-off-meets-live-translation/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/a-cartoon-of-two-people-talking-in-google-meets-with-the-translation-showing-english-to-spanish.jpg" length="80" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Meet]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Talk together in different languages.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Google has pulled back the curtain on how it developed the live translation feature for Google Meet. The company’s audio engineering and product management teams, along with Google DeepMind, were able to achieve what was apparently a five-year goal in just two years.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 19:55:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/google-explains-how-it-pulled-off-meets-live-translation/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[5 Family Car Options to Lease For Under $300 Per Month in 2025]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/5-surprising-family-cars-you-can-lease-for-under-300-a-month-in-2025/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Brent vd Schyff]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/large-62544-2025konaelectric.jpg" length="4848" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hyundai]]></category><category><![CDATA[Volkswagen]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mazda]]></category><category><![CDATA[Toyota]]></category><category><![CDATA[Nissan]]></category><category><![CDATA[LEGO]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Could Volkswagen be the number one family car to lease for under $300?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>We're living in uncertain times. <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/tariffs-reshaping-auto-industry-life-after/" target="_blank">Tariffs are playing havoc</a> with the automotive industry.<span class="display-card-hyperlink-article" data-id="2011714"><a href="/ev-tax-credit-irs-second-shot/" target="_blank">EV tax credits</a></span> that have been utilized to stimulate the adoption across all EV manufacturers are coming to a halt. Fast. At first glance, you might think this is a bad thing, but let me assure you that it isn't. One thing we've learned is that from chaos comes opportunity.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 19:31:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/5-surprising-family-cars-you-can-lease-for-under-300-a-month-in-2025/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Apple Watch Series 11 vs. Ultra 3: Which Apple Wearable Should You Pick?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/apple-watch-series-11-vs-apple-watch-ultra-3/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/the-apple-watch-ultra-3.jpg" length="2912" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple Watch Ultra 3]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple Watch Series 11]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple Watch]]></category><category><![CDATA[Wearables]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The answer probably depends on whether you own a GoPro.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Apple has refreshed the Watch lineup with the Ultra 3, which arrived alongside the base model Series 11. Whether you’re new to the world of wearables or thinking about an upgrade, these models occupy a similar place in the market but ultimately serve a different purpose.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 19:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/apple-watch-series-11-vs-apple-watch-ultra-3/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[4 Accessories That Won’t Work With the iPhone 17 and 17 Pro]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/accessories-that-wont-work-with-the-iphone-17-and-17-pro/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apple-iphone-17-lenses-in-a-row.jpg" length="1191" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone Air]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 16]]></category><category><![CDATA[battery]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Apple just introduced an accessory that won't work with the iPhone 17.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Treating yourself to a new iPhone this year? You might be disappointed to learn that you can’t necessarily bring all your old accessories with you. This even includes a brand-new Apple accessory that was announced at the very same event.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 18:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/accessories-that-wont-work-with-the-iphone-17-and-17-pro/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Grab a Galaxy Watch 8 Classic for 28% Off Today]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/grab-a-galaxy-watch-8-classic-for-28-off-today/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/person-holding-the-samsung-galaxy-watch-8-classic-54642292373-o-1.jpg" length="387" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Deals]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy Watch8 Classic]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            One of the best smartwatches you can get for an Android phone.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Samsung's newest high-end wearable, the Galaxy Watch 8 Classic, has just received a major discount. Normally priced at $500, you can now get this high-quality smartwatch for just <a href="https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/3607085/type/dlg/sid/UUhtgUeUpU2016485/https://www.woot.com/offers/new-samsung-galaxy-watch-8-classic-smartwatch-2025z" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">$360 on Woot</a>. This is a massive 28% off, and perfect for anyone who wants a smartwatch with a classic rotating bezel.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 17:53:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/grab-a-galaxy-watch-8-classic-for-28-off-today/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[IPhone 17 Pro vs. Samsung Galaxy S25 Ultra: Which Is the Best Flagship?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/iphone-17-pro-vs-samsung-galaxy-s25-ultra/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Shikhar Mehrotra]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/iphone-17-pro-vs-galaxy-s25-ultra.png" length="958" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17 Pro]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy S25 Ultra]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            With hardware like this, there's no wrong answer.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The iPhone 17 Pro is here, featuring a new unibody design, a more powerful A19 Pro chipset, an enhanced camera setup, and various other upgrades. But does it have what it takes to beat the Galaxy S25 Ultra? Let's find out.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 17:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/iphone-17-pro-vs-samsung-galaxy-s25-ultra/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Plugged In—Best Retro TV Shows That Toyed With Virtual Reality]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/retro-tv-shows-that-toyed-with-virtual-reality/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mark McPherson]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/retro-style-illustration-showing-vintage-vr-headsets-with-scenes-from-classic-tv-shows.png" length="461" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Tubi]]></category><category><![CDATA[Tech Throwback]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Dive into the fascinating world of virtual reality as seen in these 10 throwback TV shows that predicted it.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Before <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/category/virtual-reality/" target="_blank">virtual reality</a> was a common gaming platform, it was seen as a wondrous new tech. Wearing that bulky visor with all the wires connected felt like delving into an entirely new world, even if it was one composed of limited polygons. With this innovation came our own speculation of what could possibly lie behind the corners of this digital frontier.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 16:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/retro-tv-shows-that-toyed-with-virtual-reality/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Gmail Is Making It Easier to Track Packages and Find Deals]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/gmail-is-making-it-easier-to-track-packages-and-find-deals/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Joe Fedewa]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/gmail-logo-pattern-1.jpg" length="785" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Gmail]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A new tab in Gmail will simplify your online shopping experience.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Navigating an email inbox isn’t fun, and Google is constantly trying to improve how that works in Gmail. The latest updates will make it easier to find and track all your purchases, as well as find good deals among the piles of clutter.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2025 16:01:43 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/gmail-is-making-it-easier-to-track-packages-and-find-deals/</guid></item></channel>
